<TEXT>
<P>
The Paris-Dakar rally moved into Sebha, the boyhood home of Libyan leader 
Moammar Kadafi, with Belgian Jacky Ickx holding the automobile lead and 
Spaniard Carlos Mas edging ahead in the motorcycle division. 
</P>
<P>
Upon reaching the checkpoint after a day's drive through the desert, exhausted 
rally drivers were greeted with promises from Kadafi for a special New Year's 
Eve day banquet for the racers and for permission to exclude the drivers and 
their support teams from the ban on alcohol in his Islamic society. 
</P>
